  "texts": [
    "The discrepancy may be attributed to the inherently critical nature of feedback, which can elicit negative emotions regardless of the source.",
    "Furthermore, some participants perceived AI feedback as inherently inferior to human feedback, citing its lack of personalization and empathy as significant drawbacks.",
    "It is also worth considering that the feedback process itself-whether AI-generated or human-can sometimes be emotionally taxing for students.",
    "Previous research by McGarrell and Verbeem (2007) noted that feedback cycles, particularly when iterative or critical, can lead to emotional exhaustion.",
    "This phenomenon may be even more pronounced in the case of LLM-based feedback, perhaps due to its perceived detachment or the specific design of the study, which could have amplified these effects."
